The world is going toward a future where digital devices will become more commonplace. Everything will be done through digital devices. So instead of averting people from the usage of digital devices, we should encourage them to use that time learning something on the internet. Or if they do not like learning maybe doing something they like on the internet. Digital addiction will get more severe as time goes on, so we need find ways how we can use the time wisely we are with a digital device.
One can divert one's mind by spending times with family or by reading books

Uninstall or using different apps to refrain yourself from wasting time, do not really work. It does not work because the problem is with the person. The problem is in the inside. Meditation & the havit of reading books (hard copy) can be helpful. If anyone just develops these habits for just 2 weeks then it gets easier. First 2 weeks is the challenge.
